The paper discusses the challenges of data partitioning and replication in internet-scale services, which are typically addressed using distributed systems techniques. The focus of the paper is on group communication primitives, which are a key component of many distributed systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the performance of Multi-Ring Paxos, which is a consensus protocol used in distributed systems, suggesting that it could also be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the use of high-end networks, suggesting that it could be classified under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the performance of recovery under peak load, suggesting that it could be classified under cs.OS (Operating Systems) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
